<div class="team-members-row row">
    <div class="col-12 col-lg-3">
        <img src="http://demo.iamradical.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Samantha-Hart.jpg" class="card w-100" alt="Samantha Hart" />
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
        <h3 class=" pink-text">Samantha Hart</h3>
        <h4 class=" grey-text">Brand Advisor</h4>
        <blockquote>Being radical is about taking risks and being curious. Being an unsettled soul that is always seeking a deeper wisdom and recognizing the synchronistic moments in life - and making those connections.</blockquote>
        <p>Samantha Hart is President / CEO and Co-Founder of Foundation Content, an award-winning, full-service production company, focused on creative solutions for strategic messaging and branded content. She has been instrumental in the development of campaigns for brands such as Target, Walmart, Levi’s and Whole Foods and for a number of non-profits including United Way, Taproot Foundation, Robert Wood Johnson Foundation and Jeff Sokol's <a href="http://takepart.com" title="Take Part" target="_blank">takepart.com</a>.</p>
        <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="team-read-more pink-text" >Read More</a>
        <div class="team-more-bio" >
            <p>Before starting Foundation Content, Samantha had a successful career in the entertainment industry, which began under the mentorship of David Geffen at his venerable record label, Geffen Records working on projects for bands like Nirvana, Guns 'N Roses and Aerosmith. She went on to become Creative Director at Gramercy Pictures (now Focus Films). Samantha’s creative vision brought prominence to such small independent features as “Dead Man Walking,” “Fargo,” “The Usual Suspects,” and “Four Weddings And A Funeral.” She continued her successful run of hits at Fox Searchlight with “Waking Ned Devine” and “Boys Don’t Cry” before moving to Universal Pictures as Senior Vice President of Marketing and Advertising.</p>
            <p>Ms. Hart has won numerous awards for both her creative writing and design including the prestigious Gold Hugo Award for her work on United Way.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
        <hr/>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="team-members-row row">
    <div class="col-12 col-lg-3">
        <img src="http://demo.iamradical.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Sylvaine-Falque.png" class="card w-100" alt="Sylvaine Falque" />
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
        <h3 class=" pink-text">Sylvaine Falque</h3>
        <h4 class=" grey-text">Brand Advisor</h4>
        <blockquote>What I like about being Radical? Radical people can move mountains. They see positives in every situtaion, barriers and 'No's' as challenges, changes as oppurtunities, new encounters as gifts. They make life full, exciting, generous. I definitely want to be one of them.</blockquote>
        <p>Sylvaine Falque brings substantial experience in the development of a range of prestige cosmetic brands, highlighted by her 20 years at Estée Lauder.</p>
        <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="team-read-more pink-text" >Read More</a>
        <div class="team-more-bio" >
            <p>From 2006 to 2010, Sylvaine Falque served as General Manager Estee Lauder Companies in France. In this capacity, she helped develop a wide portfolio of prestige brands on the French market : Estee lauder, Clinique, Tom Ford, La Mer, Bobbi Brown, Jo Malone, Mac, and Goodskins Lab. From 1989 to 2006 she was Marketing Manager, then General Manager with the Clinique brand, which became one of the major forces in the market under her leadership. She has also been instrumental in developing the Breast Cancer Awareness program and making the pink ribbon the symbol of that cause in France.</p>
            <p>Sylvaine started her career with Revlon in the USA, then joined Pierre Fabre as Marketing Manager for Rene Furterer, a multi-channel prestige hair care brand.</p>
            <p>Throughout her career, Sylvaine has acquired an in-depth knowledge of the drivers of cosmetics in different channels of distribution : prestige perfumeries and department stores, pharmacies, hair salons, retail stores and e-commerce. She has been able to create strong long-term relationships with colleagues, retailers and suppliers. She has been recognized for her strategic vision, result driven attitude and leadership.</p>
            <p>Sylvaine holds an MBA from Columbia University, in Marketing and Finance, and a BA from Marseille’s School of Management.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
        <hr/>
    </div>
